assy in Nicosia and is expected to do so in 2015.\nBULLET::::- Cyprus Foreign Affairs: List of bilateral treaties with Syria\n-valign=\"top\"\nCyprus is represented in Vietnam through its embassy in New Delhi, India. Vietnam is represented in Cyprus through its embassy in Tripoli, Libya.\n\nCyprus' 1990 application for full EU membership caused a storm in the Turkish Cypriot community, which argued that the move required their consent. Following the December 1997 EU Summit decisions on EU enlargement, accession negotiations began 31 March 1998. Cyprus joined the European Union on 1 May 2004. To fulfil its commitment as a member of the European Union, Cyprus withdrew from the Non-Aligned Movement on accession, retaining observer status.\n\n!width=\"15%\" Country\n!width=\"12%\" Formal relations began\n!Notes\n-valign=\"top\"\nBULLET::::- Both countries established diplomatic relations on 28 August 1991.\nBULLET::::- Albania is represented in Cyprus by its embassy in Athens, Greece and an honorary consulate in Larnaca.\nBULLET::::- Cyprus is represented in Albania by its embassy in Athens, Greece and an honorary consulate in Tirane.\nBULLET::::- Both countries have a number of bilateral agreements.\n-valign=\"top\"\n\nBULLET::::- Bulgaria has an embassy in Nicosia, and honorary consulate in Limassol.\nBULLET::::- Cyprus has an embassy in Sofia.\nBULLET::::- Cyprus joined the European Union as a full member on 1 May 2004, while Bulgaria joined on 1 January 2007.\nBULLET::::- Cyprus Foreign Affairs: List of bilateral treaties with Bulgaria\n-valign=\"top\"\n1960sSee Cyprus–Czech Republic relations\n\nBULLET::::- Cyprus has an embassy in Prague.\nBULLET::::- The Czech Republic has an embassy in Nicosia and 2 honorary consulates (in Limassol and Nicosia).\nBULLET::::- Both countries are full members of the European Union.\nBULLET::::- Cyprus Foreign Affairs: List of bilateral treaties with the Czech Republic\n-valign=\"top\"\n\nBULLET::::- Cyprus has an embassy in Copenha